<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Keemen of BB</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-09-11 09:12:32</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>I am using two of this, and Yes the stats are correct, they are very fine blades.  Now for getting them it is very easy with a good group, you will need Enchanter, Cleric, Warrior (tank), and a Evac'er...  It is in the Pyramid Area by Bridge 2,  you have 3 scarbs (beetles), 2 frogs, 2 roamer,  and by the pyramid there are 2 more frogs, and you can pull them with out arrgo'ing the Golem that is on top of the Pyramid.  To pull the Golem I stand on the two rock just left in the mouth of the cave and pull the golem with a arrow.<BR>
<BR>
Now, what I have been able to achieve with this weap, I dont have to taunt anymore,  the damage output is outstanding...  Im able to hit harder and faster then a ranger 3 lvls higher then myself...  Also we got two of these in one night hunting, and I have seen 4 drop so far,  but I have never seen the wind saber that it is rumored to drop that is a Ranger only weap 13/22.<BR>
<BR>
Keemen Dion'Mraane<BR>
Clachan Brigh<BR>
52 warrior<BR>
Bristlebane server</font></td></tr></table>
